Start your  2023 BIG - Come join the Astro Fam! 

For the past month I've been secretly renovating a brand-new addition to our studio and am now looking for artists, designers, painters, sculptors, and beyond to join the gang. 

This new space has lots of room to build around your needs and I'm open to how you want it to operate - fresh start! 💞 Units can be shared between two artists.

Additionally, there is a unit available in the main space, which is more open concept and communal. If you're looking to cross-pollinate with some of Vancouver's most exciting artists, this one's for you. 

This is a non-profitable pursuit, simply aimed to create the most fertile creative ground for artists to flourish.

Viewings available by request:
Dec 29th 11am-8pm
Dec 30th 11am-8pm
Jan 3rd/onward 11am-8pm

Pressure creates diamonds. @mark_illing under pressure creates wonder and miracles. 

Leading up to painting the 11k sq/ft pool installation, 'The Bathing Dyad' for @bosaproperties / @kingswood.properties in the second heat wave of 2021, @jrdnkallman / @tsc_agency knocked on our door to see if he could turn it up even more. 

The Mission: Create 15 unique animated NFTs to be embedded into @infiniteobjects frames as giveaways as part of a private soiree series for the epic launch of 1515. Each work would begin and end visually echoing my mural design for @vanmuralfest, then break free into it's own unique chromatic chaos. 

Mark was limited to a 2.5-week turnaround to make absolute magic. Through countless sleepless nights, render failures, graphics card supply chain suffocation, and constant creative beratement by yours truly, Mark and a team of Russian render farms got us over the finish line in the twelfth hour. 

See them all at opensea.io/collection/thebathingdyad

Finally!

At the last 2019 edition, Pablo and I had the pleasure of showing the collection to Doug Coupland, whose socks were immediately blown off, then, forever vaporized into time and space.  Astounded by the artistic spectacle, he was quick to ask how he could get involved and support. In turn, both Pablo’s and my own socks not only shot off our feet, but rocketed into a heart-shaped, smoke-tailed trajectory, terminating into a fiery kiss at it’s
centre.

We were excited.

A year and half later, through fluctuating public health regulations, busy schedules, renovations, and life, the creative spectacle is returning bigger and brighter than ever. Join us January 27th for the super merger of artists, curators, and incredible new host venue — MNP Tower, 1021 West Hastings. The exhibit is generously supported and produced by Oxford Properties, thank you so much. See you there <3

Artwork by @pabloz74

Off tomorrow to deliver this monster commission to a masterclass in residential architecture, 'TidePool' by famed Brian L Hemingway.

'Confluence' was created to echo and amplify the property's marriage of Eastern and Western design traits. The work deconstructs and reconstructs the interior of Kyoto's Shokin-tei tea house (1658) into a balance of antiquity and modernity.

 A ground-trembling thank you to Ben Levitt and Maria Espinosa at @plaidfoxstudio for the challenge, and more so their trust in this. Working often with architecturally informed abstraction already, the design development felt incredibly natural. But I felt approaching this subject matter needed to go further than the traditional 2-dimensional painting. Before pigment hit the panel, I learned and developed many new textural techniques, some similar to scenic painting. Areas that I felt could be flat, now had volume and life. Incredible journey, would recommend.  

'Confluence' / Acrylics / 69"x86.5"

I’ve finally recovered from the 5-hour spectacle of cartwheeling handshakes and footshakes at the launch of @100amigosartshow last Friday.

Thank you to everyone who came or had us in their hearts — such an incredibly warm and positively overwhelming response. Oh, man.

Thank you, @pabloz74 , for allowing me to team up back in 2019. This collaboration created a profound current, which fortunately was met by @douglascoupland who saw it’s energy and potential.

Though our ‘youthful’ internal working title ‘100 Amigos, Fuck Yes’ was left on the cutting room floor, the sentiment remained intact.

Fuck Yes. 2023 is going to be fucking powerful. 
_

Artists, you didn’t just show up, you stepped up to flex for Vancouver — world-class, bravo! Moving forward, I have my fingers crossed for a 250 Amigos next year, it will make curating this show a lot less excruciating. 

This wouldn’t have been possible without the generosity and support of @oxfordpropertiesgroupyvr and Jason Mcwhinnie. Thank you, we are so grateful to have you take 100 Amigos to the next level.

Huge love to @cincodrinkco @nightingalerest , Brass Fish and Free House for the amazing libations <3<3<3

Our exhibition wall was constructed by the lovely folks at @gnwsshop The show was hung with expert care by @nickpound , @_aimeeyoung and @ouiouimaybe You all made my brain at ease.

The night also marked the launch of my new company @OpalProjects Mural and Art Production House with partners @fourhundredml, @Brotherjopa and Steff Love. We’ve put our knowledge and experience into one place and are excited to make magic. More to come…

Steff you bent time and space to make this happen. Your leadership, organization and emotional support allowed the exhibition to backflip over the finish line. ♥️

Finally, I couldn’t have done it without you @chrstsn_ Thank you for loving me and supporting me through the chaos. Love you.

Photography by @_brandonartis

Find it behind 163 West 4th Ave, Vancouver

Big collab with my art school bubby/roommate/guidance counsellor @workingtitledesign. It's a bit of a change of tact to say the least from our previous project, The Present is a Gift, 2016.

I felt tired of just putting pictures walls and made this composition around site specificity. Negative space and mark economy around gas lines and power, parking line integration, and a very expensive (but worth it) fluorescent entrance to where the minds of Astro Studio create. 

Huge thank you to Astro Studio member, and legendarily talented illustrator/ @thecoalcinder_o who froze half to death in a makeshift pool we built behind the studio for the reference materials. 

💓 @brotherjopa for tackling technical direction for all of Astro Alley

Prodigy. I couldn't resist. 

Supported by @vanmuralfest

FLUX
763 Hornby, Vancouver
2023

Big thanks to the team at @caffeartigiano and Dax at @paradeagency for the opportunity and trust - great to have something living downtown  ❤️

The work was designed asymmetrically, but the adjacent mirror-clad wall filled the space with some interesting improvisational symmetry. I realized the work has a tangential relationship with the Vancouver Art Gallery across the street. In 2019 I produced and co-wrote a short film with the babe @chrstsn_ which was projection-mapped onto it's facade in collaboration with Burrard Arts Foundation for Facade Festival 2019. At the end of the piece, the evolving floral interstitials by Mark Illing were mirrored to create a sense of unity between the characters of the piece.

Big love to my mural brother @jsiloh for all the tricky bits, and @col.urr for everything in between on the wall 🙏❤️🙌 

Honourable mention to the old woman who accosted me for multiple days, convinced I was some sort of paranoid, non-Canadian, who could be physically prodded at her whym 💋
